<!-- FULL_ARTICLE -->

Starting gold from social class (character.rs); race-group parent-occupation tables (§1–§6) on this page.

Social class (1–100) is rolled from race-group background charts during history generation (`character_get_history`). It mainly sets starting gold and flavor text. Umoria start gold (`player_calculate_start_gold`):

`social_class * 6 + 1d25 + 325 − Σ(5×(stat−10) for STR/INT/WIS/CON/DEX) + 5×(CHR−10)`, plus +50 if female, floor 80.

Parent-occupation tables below are from Beej `classes.txt` (John Thornton). Final SC is clamped to 1–100.

--[ §1 Humans, Half-Elves, Half-Orcs ]---------------------------------------

```
Occupation        base   Birth              adj   Family            adj
Serf              16–19  1st child          +5    Well-liked        +5
Yeoman            31–34  1 of several        0    Credit to family   0
Townsman          41–44  Illegit. acknow.  −10    Black sheep      −35
Guildsman         56–59  Illegit. unack.   −20
Landed Knight     71–74  Adopted*          −20
Titled Noble      81–84
Royal Bloodline   91–94
```

\*Adopted applies to half-orcs only (all half-orcs are adopted).

Half-elf elvish-parent adj: Green ♀0/♂+5, Grey ♀+5/♂+10, High ♀+15/♂+20.

